e\nChicago Board of Trade\nAmerican Bankers Association\nDistrict Bankers Association\nHlfiBS\nRational 0540 WASHINGTON, D. G\n\u2014l\naxle generating system to supply\nthe electric lights in that-car.\n\u201cWith the increasing uau, w\nsaid the report, submitted by\nthe committee on locomotive*\nand car lighting, of eleetrie\ncurrent on our passenger train\ncars for lighting and other pur\nposes and the absolute necessity\nfor a full supply of that isur\nrent at all times, it to quite\nevident that, particularly in\nthe northern sections of the\ncountry, an improvement over\nthe belt drive as now used to\nnecessary.\n\u201cWhere snow and ice are\npresent, belt slippage has bo\ncome fatal to good and satisfac\ntory generator performance.\u201d\nBirmim\nFOR OIL FIRM\nA tax abatement of 81,016.567\nwas granted the Atlantic Refin\ning Co., of Philadelphia by the\nTreasury today.\nOther abatements were:\nPublic Service Corp., New\nYersey, 8141,177.\nChile Copper Co., New York.\n8119.534.\nElton Corporation, New York,\n870,644. I\nSharon Steel Hoop Co., Sharon,\nPa., 868,173.\nFrank Sb Seder, Pittsburgh,\n864.788.\nAnita M. Baldwin, Los Angeles,\n834.121.\nHome Building Sb Savings Co.,\nToledo, 830,186.\nPot Elea Power yfd.....|11\u00bb ;ill%\nPot El\u00abc Pwr pfd |10\u00ab%|l\u00abt\nWaih Ry A Sloe com t|(o 1....,\nWash Ry A El pfd ..J It I 12\nWaah Balto A An e0m....l t I\nWaah Balt A An pfd. I t I\nNntionol \u00bbtonh Stocfca\nCapital ..|23\u00bb itit\nColumbia 1\n\u2022Commercial (atamped) 12!T%|24\u00ab\n\u2022Dlatrict |3IS |2tt\nFederal-American ...........|3tt\nJ.ibery |2ot |22#\n\u2022Lincoln |4\u00ab\u00ab |43i\n\u2022Metropolitan 24t 230\nRigga |44t 1435\nSecond 130 |2l\nWaahlnglon 250 I.\nTroat Company m\u2014fco I I\nAm Sec A Tr Co 2\u00abt |3M\nContfnental Truat 120 |l4O\n\u2022March Bank A Truat fl2t |l4O\nNational Sav A Tr |530 |*7s\nUnion Truat |2lt i2Tt\nWash Loan A Tr......... ,|4st 1310\nBnvlnga a\u2014lt Stacfcp '~l I\n\u2022Bank of Bethesda ~...7.1