ments, 8193,000,000 in Govern\nmsnt deposits and 846,000,000 in\ntime deposits, and decreases of\n848.000,000 in net demand deposits\nand $4,000,000 in borrowings from\nFederal Reserve banks.\nLoans on securities, which at all\nreporting banks were 851,000,000\nabove the previous week\u2019s total,\nincreased 887,000,000 in the New\nYork district and 88,000,000 in the\nChicago district, and declined\n813.000.000 in the Boston district,\n811.000,000 in the Kansas City\ndistrict and 810.000,000 in the\nCleveland district. \u201cAU other\u201d\nloans Increased 850,000,000 in the\nNew York district, 832.000,000 in\nthe Chicago district, 815,000.000\nin the Cleveland district and <lll.-\n000.000 at aU reporting banks.\nHoldings of U. 8. Government\nsecurities increased 825,000,000 in\nthe New York district. 812,000,000\nin the Philadelphia district, 811,*\n000,000 in the Richmond district,\n810,000.000 in the Cleveland dis\ntrict and 873,000 000 at all report\ning banks. Holdings of other se\ncurities declined 812,000,000 in\nthe New York district and in\ncreased 87,000,000 in the Chicago\ndistrict, while aU reporting banks\nshow no net change for the week.\nBorrowings from Federal Re\nserve banks changed relatively\nlittle in the various Federal Re\nserve districts, total borrowings of\naU reporting banks on June 18 ag\ngregating 844,000,000 as compared\nwith 848,000.000 the week before.\nSteel Sheet Tonnage\nDrops During May\nNEW YORH, June 24.\u2014Produc\ntion of steel sheets in May totaled\n274,220 tohs, as compared with\n308,998 tons in April, according\nto the National Association of\nFlat RoUed Steel Manufacturers.\nThe output was at 73% per\ncent of the capacity of reporting\nmakers, as compared with 84 per\ncent in April. Sales during May\namounted to 204,589 tons, as com\npared with 300,086 tons in April,\nand shipments were 266,436 tons\nand 291,601 tons, respectively.\nUnfilled tonnage on June 1 was\n461,756 tons, as compared with\n526.827 tons a month previous.\nTotal sheet capacity of the United\nStates for May was about 558,800\ntons, the capacity on which the\nabove figures are based.\nAdam A. Weuebler A San. AnetlmiMra\nHOUSEHOLD\nFURNITURE\nBy Order Trustee in Bankruptcy\nSmith\u2019s Transfer St Storage Co.\nalso Globa Furniture Co. for\nCharge, et al.\nPianos, Radios, Vietrolas, Dav\nenport and Bed-Davenport Suites,\nDining and Bed Room Suites,\nRugs. Chests of Drawers, Fiber\nand Wicker Furniture, Occasional\nTables and Chairs, Refrigerators,\nBreakfast Suites, I Amps. Day\nBeds, Mattresses, Personal Ef\nfects from Storage, etc.\nBy Auction\nAt WESCHLER\u2019S,\n920 Punna. Ave. N. W.\nWEDNESDAY\nJuno 25, 1830\nCommeaeinx e\u2019Clack A. M.\nCaattaning thraaxhoat the day\nAutomobile*, Inclnding ISM Graham-\nP\u00abl,\u00ab Sport Bedaa, by ardor Klwami\nM. Seal, Traatee in Bankruptcy, IS\nn\u201e MUI O 3t. N. W.\n*,jauunMnacT-\" T\nNEWS\nIn Today\u2019s\nCLASSIFIED ADS\u2014\nBBUABLB motor aervleea, body\nand fender week; general Bate re\npairing) day er night aervice; wo\nnever cloee.\nIF THE COLLECTIO.N at atampe,\neeiht er autographed lettere it\nyeur hobby, you wUI be Interested\n3a knowing of our service. We are\nleeeted at a eeaveaient downtown\naddress.\nCLEANING. MWMING AND BB\nFAIRING\u2014\u25a0Suite made to order: tar\nremodeling a Specialty i consult as\nbefore having this accessary work\ndeae. ,i\nFTBNITtTRB BBUFHOLBTBBBD\u2014\nSlip eevers made to order; aU\n1 work guaraateed; estimates ehser\nfalty gtaoa. _\nWHAT HAVB TOU7\u2014 Wo buy. sefl\nand exchange anything i eaU as and\nlet us eeme and inspect what yen\nhave ta offer and give an eetimnte\non what, w* toel B is worth.\nFBTS FOB BAt\u00df=*Uve ehameUoas.\nIseeliM. Sparrows, trees, people*.\nmhMte, goldfish, parrots, monkeys,\n\u2022etc.\nTheft are \"aidslipAts\u201d on tpmsof mmy\nhtferawbtg edoartisaiiiantt ma tei\u00df tins m\nths Business Jfsrviec-Dirsifore Os- teMg'd\nNms said BaosM OteOotfisS dSe.\nEditor\n\u2014Times Staff Photo,\nT. H