\nIs Warranted by Conditions\nBOSTON. June 24.\u2014Early and\nsubstantial recovery in general\nbusiness is forecast by the Hac-\nvard Economic Society, recognized\nas an unbiased and competent stu\ndent of conditions. In its latest\nbulletin, issued today,, the-society\nstated:\n\u201cPessimistic feeling and eon*\nflictlng tendencies not infre- r\nquently mark the formativd\nstage of recovery. Coming a*\nthis juncture with favorable\nfactors set forth in our letters\nof May 17 still operative, they\ndo not ajter our expectation of\nearly and .substantial recovery\n\u201ein general business.\n\u201cIt is not surprising that\nfears and uncertainties exist,\nfollowing business contraction.\nThere is often a stabilization\ninterval of considerable length;\nduring such interval much of\nthe business hews consists of\ndisheartening 'reports covering\noperations during preceding 3\nperiod of liquidation. Business i\nsenflknent remains, unduly pes\nsimistic at every time of the\nturn. We believe business has,\nfor some time been lit such a\nperiod of stabilization.'\n\u201cThe Washington conferences\nare likely to have important\nfavorable results within a few\nmonths. Removal of the tariff\ncontroversy will be a relief and\naid to business; effects on for,\neiga business relations may not 7\nbe so dire as predicted.\n\u201cProlonged weakness in com,\nmodify prices remains one of i\nthe most disquieting elements,\nstock prices are important fac\ntors In holding bank business\nrevival because of wide effect\non sentiment. Continued ae\ncumulation of stock for in\nvestment is a clear sign that\npresent prices are not too high\naccording to long-run appraisal\nof prudent investors.\n\u201cReduction of New York re-'.,\ndiscount rate Is a new con-\nfirmation of bank policy, and ,1\nwe believe easy money will\npersist at least through 1930.\nWhen these considerations are\nheld in view, current fears ap<\npear greater than warranted.\u201d","height":"30321","width":"24337"}}
